                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/476: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-17T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 17, 1930—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>437. Legation’s 1054, December 17, 7 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Department, studying question of possible next steps in
                        extraterritoriality negotiations, is awaiting communication from Wu
                        mentioned in your telegram under reference. Without initiating thought that
                        in the event of negotiations being delayed, Chinese Government may take some
                        unilateral action, Department desires of course to forestall any such
                        possibility. Have you any opinion, without making inquiry, as to such action
                        being in contemplation?</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Department wishes that, if possible, and without initiating an express
                        inquiry, you ascertain whether British Minister is planning any new move in
                        the matter of negotiations in near future; also is he <pb facs="0593"
                            n="495" xml:id="pg_495"/> still planning to leave China on December 30
                        as reported in Minister’s December 1, 2 p.m., from Nanking, Legation’s
                            1026?<note n="81" xml:id="d541fn81">Not printed.</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
